        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-17" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="/service_registry" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="90" x="-800" y="850" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-18" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="/election/c_2" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="80" x="-840" y="540" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-19" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="/election/c_3" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="80" x="-720" y="540" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-20" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="/election/c_4" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="80" x="-600" y="540" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-21" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Step 1&lt;/b&gt;: Nodes Volunteer to Become Leader&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Every node connected to ZooKeeper volunteers to become the leader.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Each node submits its candidacy by creating a ZNode representing itself under the election parent node.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Zookeeper maintains a global ordering, so each ZNode is assigned a sequence number based on the order it was created.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Step 2&lt;/b&gt;: Nodes Check the Election Queue&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;After creating its ZNode, each node queries the children of the election parent.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Because ZooKeeper guarantees ordering, a node can always see all ZNodes created before its own.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This allows every node to determine its position in the election sequence.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Step 3&lt;/b&gt;: Leader Selection&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Each node compares its ZNode sequence number with the others.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;If a node&#39;s ZNode has the smallest sequence number, it becomes the leader.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Otherwise, the node knows it is not the leader and waits for instructions from the elected leader.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;Efficient Leader Re-Election Strategy in ZooKeeper&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In a large distributed system, having every node watch the leader directly can create scalability problems.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Problem with the Naive Approach&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When the leader dies:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;ZooKeeper must notify all nodes in the cluster.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Every node immediately calls getChildren() to retrieve the updated list of candidate ZNodes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;After a new leader is elected, all nodes start watching the new leader&#39;s ZNode again.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;With a large number of nodes, this creates a massive spike of simultaneous requests to ZooKeeper, which can&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;overwhelm the cluster.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Improved Re-Election Design&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;To avoid overwhelming ZooKeeper, a more efficient strategy is used.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Key Idea&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Instead of every node watching the leader&#39;s ZNode:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Each node watches only the ZNode that comes immediately before it in the sequence of candidate ZNodes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;How It Works&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Initial Election&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nodes create sequential candidate ZNodes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The node with the smallest sequence number becomes the leader.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Failure Handling&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;When the leader dies:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Only the node directly after the leader in sequence is notified.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;That node calls getChildren() to verify the current ordering.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If it now owns the smallest sequence number, it becomes the new leader.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="760" width="600" x="-1560" y="-160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-22" edge="1" parent="1" source="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-5" style="endArrow=none;html=1;rounded=0;exitX=0.5;exitY=0;exitDx=0;exitDy=0;" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="-770" y="430" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="-720" y="380" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-23" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;IO Thread&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handles all the network communication with Zookeeper servers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Handles Zookeeper requests and responses&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Responds to pings&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Session Management&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Session Timeouts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;etc&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Event Thread&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manages Zookeeper events&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Connection (KeeperState.SyncConnected)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Disconnection (KeeperState.Disconnected)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Custom znode Watchers and Triggers we subscribe to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Events are executed on Event Thread in order&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="250" width="440" x="-920" y="-160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-24" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;Watchers and Triggers&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;We can register a watcher when we call the methods&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;getChildren(...)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;getData(...)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;exists(...)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The watcher allows us to get a notification when a change happens&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;getChildren(..., watcher) - Get notified when the list of a znode&#39;s children changes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;exists(znodePath, watcher) - Get notified if a znode gets deleted or created.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;getData(znodePath, watcher) - Get notified if a znode&#39;s data gets modified.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;public ZooKeeper(String connectString, int sessionTimeout, Watcher watcher) - Also takes a watcher&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Watcher registered with getChildren(), exists() and getData() are one-time triggers.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;If we want to get future notifications, we need to register the watcher again.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="760" x="40" y="-680" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-25" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;The Herd Effect&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A large number of nodes waiting for an event.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;When the event happens all nodes get notified and they all wake up&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Only one node can succeed&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Indicates bad design, can negatively impact the performance and can completely freeze the cluster.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="760" x="40" y="-480" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-26" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" value="Server&amp;nbsp;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="120" width="60" x="-1950" y="760" as="geometry" />
