        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-73" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;fontSize=15;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="40" x="-600" y="720" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-74" edge="1" parent="1" style="endArrow=classic;html=1;rounded=0;entryX=0.25;entryY=0;entryDx=0;entryDy=0;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 8;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;strokeWidth=2;" value="">
          <mxGeometry height="50" relative="1" width="50" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="-810" y="770" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="-767.5" y="850" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-75" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="getChildren()" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="30" width="90" x="-790" y="780" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-76" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Core Idea&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The system starts with a permanent ZNode called the service registry.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Whenever a node joins the cluster:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;It creates an ephemeral sequential ZNode under the service registry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Unlike leader election, these ZNodes are not empty&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Each node stores its own network address or connection information inside its ZNode.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;This forms the &lt;b&gt;service registry&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Service Discovery&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Service discovery becomes simple once all nodes are registered.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Any node that wants to discover other nodes in the cluster will:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Register a watcher on the service registry using the getChildren() method.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Read the list of registered nodes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use the getData() method to retrieve the address stored inside each ZNode.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;Whenever the cluster changes:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;A node joins&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A node leaves&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;A node crashes&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;ZooKeeper triggers a NodeChildrenChanged event, immediately notifying interested nodes.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="440" width="480" x="-1560" y="640" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-77" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Peer-to-Peer Architecture&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;with this approach, a fully peer-to-peer system can be implemented.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In this architecture:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Every node can communicate directly with any other node.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;All nodes are aware of cluster membership changes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Nodes automatically react when services appear or disappear.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;This makes the system highly dynamic and adaptive.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="160" width="480" x="-1560" y="1160" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-78" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Leader - Worker Architecture&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In a leader-worker model, the behavior is slightly different.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Workers&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Workers do not need to know about each other&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Each worker registers itself in the service registry&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Workers simply wait for tasks from the leader.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Leader&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Only the leader subscribes to registry change notifications.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The leader maintains a complete view of the cluster.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Based on the available workers, the leader distributes tasks accordingly&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If the leader fails:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;A new leader is elected&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The new leader removes itself from the worker registry.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;It continues managing and distributing work.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Why Service Discovery Matters&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Service discovery is a critical building block in distributed systems because it enables:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Automatic node discovery&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dynamic scaling&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fault tolerance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Easier cluster management&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;Nodes can be added or removed at any time without manual reconfiguration.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Important Limitation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Even with automated service discovery, nodes still need an initial way to connect to ZooKeeper.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This means some static or manual configuration is still required, such as distributing:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;ZooKeeper server addresses&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Cluster endpoints&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Initial connection settings&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;So while service discovery greatly improves scalability and automation, configuration management remains an important part of distributed systems.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="600" width="480" x="-1560" y="1520" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="MGsdMgP7l0InPqgAwvWF-79" parent="1" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#dae8fc;strokeColor=#6c8ebf;" value="Server&amp;nbsp;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="60" x="-880" y="1240" as="geometry" />
